						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone set up near the Sōmēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Jagadēkamalla II—A.D. 1146.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated in the king's <hi rend="bold">regnal year 9, Akshaya, Āshāḍha, ba. 11, Sunday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1146, July 6.</hi> The weekday was, however, <hi rend="bold">Saturday.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription is incomplete and seems to record the death of a son of Kēta following the death of <hi rend="italic">Nāḷprabhu</hi> Kēti [seṭṭi] of <hi rend="bold">Kalkere</hi> at <hi rend="bold">Sirivoḷal</hi> during a fight with the people of <hi rend="bold">Kāgenele.</hi> <hi rend="italic">Cf.</hi> No. 113 above. </p>						

						</summary>
